erator, and appear to be the most general conditions known to date\nfor which Callias' index formula has been derived.\n  Generalizations of the index formula $(*)$ to certain classes of non-Fredholm\noperators $L$ invoking the (generalized) Witten index are also discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 16 Jun 2015 20:37:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 16 Jan 2016 21:05:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-01-19"}
